comment: Terry (HOU) sets the screen on Harris (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Nowitzki (DAL) sets the screen on Brewer (HOU) from behind. Brewer rolls off and continues to defend Barea (DAL).
Anderson (DAL) cleanly blocks Ariza's (HOU) shot attempt, making contact with the ball after it has left his hands and prior to it touching the backboard.
Nowitzki (DAL) and Beverley (HOU) engage briefly while looking to establish position for the pass.
RHH shows Matthews (DAL) initiates contact and dislodges Brewer (HOU), extending his arm into him during his drive.
Pachulia (DAL) and Howard (HOU) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
Pachulia (DAL) briefly engages with Howard (HOU).
Matthews (DAL) makes incidental contact with Harden (HOU) as he catches the pass.
[Observable in enhanced video] Harden (HOU) moves his pivot foot. The official is looking for any potential illegal contact and does not pick up the pivot foot.
Beverley (HOU) moves his pivot foot.
Barea (DAL) and Howard (HOU) briefly engage during rebounding.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that possession be awarded to DAL was upheld.
Matthews (DAL) sets the screen on Ariza (HOU) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Nowitzki (DAL) and Ariza (HOU) make contact with one another while attempting to establish post position.
Nowitzki (DAL) sets the screen on Harden (HOU) within his field of vision. Harden is stationary and therefore Nowitzki does not need to give him room to avoid the contact.
Harden (HOU) makes contact with Nowitzki's (DAL) body that affects his jump shot attempt.
Matthews (DAL) clamps Harden's (HOU) arm and affects his FOM away from the ball.
Nowitzki (DAL) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Matthews (DAL) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Harden (HOU) on the perimeter.
Nowitzki (DAL) cleanly strips the ball from Harden (HOU). Any contact to an opponent's hand when it is in contact with the ball is not illegal.
Harden (HOU) commits a take foul on Harris (DAL).
Beasley (HOU) sets the screen on Matthews (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Matthews (DAL) and Harden (HOU) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
Felton (DAL) commits a take foul on Terry (HOU).
Harden (HOU) dislodges Matthews (DAL), and pushes him into Terry (HOU).
Matthews (DAL) enters the area inside the three-point line prior to the free throw being released.

[Incidental or immaterial] Matthews (DAL) knocks the ball away down the sideline. Video resolution is not clear enough to determine if he hits the ball with an open or closed hand, or if the ball hits his forearm or hand.
